1. What is the core difference between a class and an interface?

A class describes an object and its state, while an interface defines its behavioral contract.
Only one class can be inherited, but multiple interfaces can be implemented

2. Can interfaces have fields? If yes, what are the implicit modifiers for them?

Yes, they can. They are implicitly public static final

3. Can a class implement multiple interfaces? Explain why this is useful.

Yes, it allows the object to play different roles